minfi quantile normalization

###STUDY A
ann450k <- getAnnotation(IlluminaHumanMethylation450kanno.ilmn12.hg19)
targets <- read.metharray.sheet("~/Downloads/methylation/GSE61107_RAW", verbose=FALSE)
rgSet <- read.metharray.exp(targets = targets)
phenoData <- pData(rgSet)


cellCounts <- estimateCellCounts(rgSet, compositeCellType = "DLPFC",
                                 processMethod = "preprocessFunnorm", probeSelect = "auto",
                                 cellTypes = c("NeuN_neg","NeuN_pos"),
                                 referencePlatform = c("IlluminaHumanMethylation450k"),
                                 returnAll = FALSE, meanPlot = FALSE, verbose = FALSE)

MSet <- preprocessRaw(rgSet) 

#densityPlot(MSet, sampGroups = phenoData$Sample_Group)
#densityBeanPlot(MSet, sampGroups = phenoData$Sample_Group)
#par(mar=c(5,5,4,2), mgp=c(2.5,1,0), cex.main=1.5, font.main="1", fg="#6b6b6b", col.main="#4b4b4b")
#DNAmArray::screeplot(rgSet)

#All samples are kept
detP<-detectionP(rgSet) # this gets the p-values
keep <- colMeans(detP) < 0.05
rgSet <- rgSet[,keep]

# remove poor quality samples from targets data
targets <- targets[keep,]
#targets[,1:5]
# remove poor quality samples from detection p-value table
detP <- detP[,keep]
#dim(detP)

#GRset.funnorm <- preprocessFunnorm(rgSet, nPCs=5)
GRset.funnorm <- preprocessQuantile(rgSet)

# ensure probes are in the same order in the mSetSq and detP objects
detP <- detP[match(featureNames(GRset.funnorm),rownames(detP)),] 
# remove any probes that have failed in one or more samples
keep <- rowSums(detP < 0.01) == ncol(GRset.funnorm) 
filter_rgSet <- GRset.funnorm[keep,]

keep <- !(featureNames(filter_rgSet) %in% ann450k$Name[ann450k$chr %in% 
                                                         c("chrX","chrY")])
filter_rgSet <- filter_rgSet[keep,]


# remove probes with SNPs at CpG site
filter_rgSet <- dropLociWithSnps(filter_rgSet)

# exclude cross reactive probes 
filter_rgSet <- maxprobes::dropXreactiveLoci(filter_rgSet)

minfi_betas = minfi::getBeta(filter_rgSet)
myList = strsplit(colnames(minfi_betas), "_", fixed = TRUE)
new_colnames = unlist(lapply(myList,function(x) x[1]) )
colnames(minfi_betas) = new_colnames 

keeprows = intersect(rownames(minfi_betas), rownames(myNorm))
minfi_subset <- subset(minfi_betas, rownames(minfi_betas) %in% keeprows)
myNorm_subset <- subset(myNorm, rownames(myNorm) %in% keeprows)
minfi_subset =  minfi_subset[ order(match(rownames(minfi_subset), rownames(myNorm_subset))), ]

densityBeanPlot(minfi_subset, sampGroups = NULL, sampNames = NULL, main = 'Quantile normalization minfi',
                pal = brewer.pal(1, "RdBu"), numPositions = 100000)

ChAMP BMIQ

densityBeanPlot(myNorm, sampGroups = NULL, sampNames = NULL, main = 'ChAMP BMIQ',
                pal = brewer.pal(8, "Dark2"), numPositions = 100000)

colnames(minfi_df)[1] = 'beta'
minfi_df$package = 'minfi'

colnames(champ_df)[1] = 'beta'
champ_df$package = 'champ'

betaDists<- rbind(minfi_df, champ_df)
ggplot(betaDists, aes(beta, fill = package)) + 
  geom_histogram(alpha = 0.5, aes(y = ..density..), position = 'identity')

ks.test(minfi_subset[,2], myNorm_subset[,2])

## alternative hypothesis: two-sided
cor(minfi_subset[,1], myNorm_subset[,1])

Compare Champ Funnorm + SVA & Champ BMIQ + SVA

#BMIQ

myNorm_BMIQ <- champ.norm(beta=myLoad$beta,method='BMIQ',arraytype='450K',cores=3)
mod = model.matrix(~Sample_Group+Sex+Age+PMI,data=phenoData)
mod0 = mod[,-c(2)] 
n.sv<-num.sv(myNorm_BMIQ, mod, method = "be", vfilter = 5000, B = 20, seed = NULL)
n =n.sv
sva = svaseq(myNorm_BMIQ,mod,mod0, n.sv =n)$sv 
## Number of significant surrogate variables is:  2 
## Iteration (out of 5 ):1  2  3  4  5
colnames(sva)<-paste("sv", 1:n, sep = "")
pd_sva<-cbind(phenoData,sva)

#Correct known and unknown confounders
design = model.matrix(~Sample_Group+Sex+Age+sv1+sv2,data=pd_sva)
Y<-myNorm_BMIQ
X<-as.matrix(design)
beta = (solve(t(X)%*%X)%*%t(X))%*%t(Y)
myRegress= Y - t(X[,c(3:ncol(X))] %*% beta[c(3:nrow(beta)),])


myNorm_BMIQ_beta <- myRegress
champ_dmp_bmiq= champ.DMP(beta = myNorm_BMIQ_beta, pheno=phenoData$Sample_Group, compare.group=c("SCZ","N"), adjPVal=.05,arraytype = "450K")
##       Contrasts
## Levels pSCZ-pN
##   pN        -1
##   pSCZ       1
#FUNCTIONAL

myNorm_func <- champ.norm(beta=myLoad$beta, rgSet=rgSet, method='FunctionalNormalization',arraytype='450K',cores=3)
mod = model.matrix(~Sample_Group+Sex+Age+PMI,data=phenoData)
mod0 = mod[,-c(2)] 
n.sv<-num.sv(myNorm_func, mod, method = "be", vfilter = 5000, B = 20, seed = NULL)
n =n.sv
sva = svaseq(myNorm_func,mod,mod0, n.sv =n)$sv 
## Number of significant surrogate variables is:  2 
## Iteration (out of 5 ):1  2  3  4  5
colnames(sva)<-paste("sv", 1:n, sep = "")
pd_sva<-cbind(phenoData,sva)

#Correct known and unknown confounders
design = model.matrix(~Sample_Group+Sex+Age+sv1+sv2,data=pd_sva)
Y<-myNorm_func
X<-as.matrix(design)
beta = (solve(t(X)%*%X)%*%t(X))%*%t(Y)
myRegress= Y - t(X[,c(3:ncol(X))] %*% beta[c(3:nrow(beta)),])

myNorm_func_beta <- myRegress
champ_dmp_func= champ.DMP(beta = myNorm_func_beta, pheno=phenoData$Sample_Group, compare.group=c("SCZ","N"), adjPVal=.05,arraytype = "450K")
##       Contrasts
## Levels pSCZ-pN
##   pN        -1
##   pSCZ       1
vlist <- list(rownames(champ_dmp_func$SCZ_to_N), rownames(champ_dmp_bmiq$SCZ_to_N))
names(vlist) <- c("champ_func", "champ_bmiq")
myCol <- brewer.pal(3, "Pastel2")

plt=venn.diagram(vlist, 
                 filename=NULL,
                 imagetype="png",
                 cex = 1,
                 cat.cex = 1,
                 lwd = 2,
                 fill=myCol[1:2])

grid.newpage()
grid.draw(plt)

pcs=5

qc.summary <- meffil.qc.summary(qc.objects, verbose=F)
## [meffil.qc.summary] Wed Oct 26 02:24:51 2022 Sex summary FALSE
#meffil.qc.report(qc.summary, output.file="qc/report.html")

#Remove bad samples

outlier <- qc.summary$bad.samples
table(outlier$issue)
## 
##      Sex mismatch X-Y ratio outlier 
##                 2                 1
index <- outlier$issue %in% c("Control probe (dye.bias)", 
                              "Methylated vs Unmethylated",
                              "X-Y ratio outlier",
                              "Low bead numbers",
                              "Detection p-value",
                              "Sex mismatch",
                              "Genotype mismatch",
                              "Control probe (bisulfite1)",
                              "Control probe (bisulfite2)")

outlier <- outlier[index,]


#Remove outliers
qc.objects <- meffil.remove.samples(qc.objects, outlier$sample.name)


#Normalize

norm.objects <- meffil.normalize.quantiles(qc.objects, number.pcs=pcs)
norm.beta <- meffil.normalize.samples(norm.objects, cpglist.remove=qc.summary$bad.cpgs$name)


minfi_betas = minfi::getBeta(filter_rgSet)
myList = strsplit(colnames(minfi_betas), "_", fixed = TRUE)
new_colnames = unlist(lapply(myList,function(x) x[1]) )
colnames(minfi_betas) = new_colnames 

keeprows = intersect(rownames(minfi_betas), rownames(norm.beta))
minfi_subset <- subset(minfi_betas, rownames(minfi_betas) %in% keeprows)
norm.beta.subset <- subset(norm.beta, rownames(norm.beta) %in% keeprows)
minfi_subset =  minfi_subset[ order(match(rownames(minfi_subset), rownames(norm.beta.subset))), ]

minfi_df = as.data.frame(minfi_subset[,2])
colnames(minfi_df)[1] = 'beta'
minfi_df$package = 'minfi'

meffil_df = as.data.frame(norm.beta.subset[,2])
colnames(meffil_df)[1] = 'beta'
meffil_df$package = 'meffil'

betaDists<- rbind(minfi_df, meffil_df)
ggplot(betaDists, aes(beta, fill = package)) + 
  geom_histogram(alpha = 0.5, aes(y = ..density..), position = 'identity')
